/*
5.1a)

Let T represent the program terminating
Let N represent variable n becoming 0
Let M represent variable m becoming 0

The argument is (¬T ⋁ N) ⋀ (N ⇒ M) ⋀ T  ⇒  M

It is a theorem by the following proof.
*/

  (¬T ⋁ N) ⋀ (N ⇒ M) ⋀ T
=    〈 Absorption (3.44a) 〉
  N ⋀ (N ⇒ M) ⋀ T
=    〈 (3.66) 〉
  N ⋀ M ⋀ T
⇒    〈 (3.76b) Strengthening 〉
  M ╱╱

