/*
5.1c)

Let M represent a man being on the moon.
Let C represent the moon being made of cheese.
Let I represent the statement "I am a monkey."

The argument is (M ⇒ C) ⋀ (C ⇒ I) ⋀ (¬M ⋁ ¬C)  ⇒  ¬C ⋁ I

It is a theorem by the following proof.
*/

  (M ⇒ C) ⋀ (C ⇒ I) ⋀ (¬M ⋁ ¬C)
⇒    〈 Strengthening (3.76b) 〉
  C ⇒ I
=    〈 (3.59) Implication 〉
  ¬C ⋁ I  ╱╱


